    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) recommends that vets send samples to a laboratory on this list.</p>
      <p>These laboratories meet one or more of the following specifications:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>ISO/IEC 17025 accredited</li>
        <li>UKAS accredited (UK accredited) for an enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) or PRRS polymerase chain reaction (PCR) test</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A farmer will not be eligible for funding unless samples are tested at a laboratory that meets at least one of these specifications.</p>
      <p>If you have a question about laboratories used for review testing, or want to be added to this list, contact the RPA by email or phone.</p>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:ruralpayments@defra.gov.uk" class="govuk-link">ruralpayments@defra.gov.uk</a></p>
      <p>Telephone: 03000 200 301<br> Monday to Friday, 8:30am to 5pm, except bank holidays<br></p>
